<%# ============================ CASE STUDY: ARGOSY ============================ %>
<%# Argosy Foundation / FIRST Robotics case study. %>
<section class="mk-section mk-product mk-product--metric">
  <div class="mk-container">
    <div class="mk-product__grid">
      <div class="mk-product__copy">
        <p class="mk-eyebrow">Case study &middot; Argosy Foundation</p>
        <h2 class="mk-section__title">
          Supporting hundreds of organizations shouldn't require managing hundreds of grants.
        </h2>
        <p class="mk-lead">
          The <a href="https://www.argosyfnd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Argosy
          Foundation</a>, founded by John Abele (co-founder of Boston Scientific), set out to
          fund FIRST Robotics teams nationwide. Today, thanks to HCB's financial
          infrastructure, more than 500 teams receive funding every year through a single,
          transparent grantmaking program.
        </p>
        <p class="mk-lead">
          Beyond handling grant distribution, administration, and compliance, HCB gives the
          Argosy Foundation something a year-end report never could: a real-time,
          grant-by-grant view of where their funding goes and the impact it's creating, with
          less overhead, not more.
        </p>
        <ul class="mk-ticks">
          <li>Skip the grantmaking staff and back-office admin</li>
          <li>See how every team spends its grant, in real time</li>
          <li>Fund 500 teams with the effort of funding one</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mk-product__media">
        <div class="mk-metric">
          <p class="mk-metric__num">500+</p>
          <p class="mk-metric__label">FIRST Robotics teams funded every year</p>
          <ul class="mk-metric__list">
            <li>One grantmaking program</li>
            <li>Nationwide reach</li>
            <li>Real-time reporting on every grant</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mk-metric__source">
            <a href="https://www.argosyfnd.org" class="mk-metric__logo-link" target="_blank"
               rel="noopener" aria-label="Argosy Foundation (opens in a new tab)">
              <%= image_tag "https://cdn.hackclub.com/019e8960-f2f5-7575-b448-3acb94a77a82/image.png",
                    class: "mk-metric__logo", alt: "Argosy Foundation",
                    loading: "lazy", decoding: "async" %>
            </a>
            <span class="mk-metric__detail">Founded by John Abele, co-founder of Boston Scientific</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ==================== ORGANIZATIONS ON HCB (live portfolio explorer) ==================== %>
<%# Replaces the old standalone Reboot / Public Grids / "Where it lands" sections with one
    interactive showcase of real recipient organizations that *run on* HCB — deliberately
    distinct from the funder proof (Argosy case study + "In good company" marquee) so the two
    kinds of organization never read as the same thing. A vertical rail selects an org; the
    stage on the right swaps to its detail. The final "wildcard" rail item reframes the list as
    a sample: your giving isn't limited to these orgs, or even to orgs already on HCB.

    Recipients + field docs live in MarketingHelper#funder_recipients. Driven by
    funders_portfolio_controller (mirrors the value-pillar explorer's a11y pattern). With no JS
    every panel renders stacked, so nothing is hidden. %>
<% recipients = funder_recipients(show_public_grids: @show_public_grids) %>
<% wildcard_index = recipients.length %>
<section class="mk-section mk-section--alt mk-portfolio-section">
  <div class="mk-container">
    <div class="mk-portfolio" data-controller="funders-portfolio"
         data-action="keydown->funders-portfolio#keydown mouseenter->funders-portfolio#hoverIn mouseleave->funders-portfolio#hoverOut">
      <%# Left column: heading + rail. Keeping the heading in-column (rather than in a full-width
          band above the grid) fills what would otherwise be dead space to the right of it, and
          lets the detail stage rise to a full-height hero on the right. %>
      <div class="mk-portfolio__aside">
        <div class="mk-portfolio__head">
          <p class="mk-eyebrow">Already on HCB</p>
          <h2 class="mk-section__title">A few of the thousands of organizations already running on HCB.</h2>
          <p class="mk-portfolio-count">
            <span data-funders-portfolio-target="count"><%= @stats[:organizations] %></span>
            organizations &middot; since <%= @stats[:founded] %>
          </p>
        </div>

        <%# --- rail: selectable list of orgs, ending in the open-door wildcard --- %>
        <div class="mk-portfolio__rail" role="tablist" aria-label="Organizations on HCB" aria-orientation="vertical">
        <% recipients.each_with_index do |org, i| %>
          <button type="button" class="mk-portfolio__item" role="tab" id="mk-port-tab-<%= i %>"
                  aria-controls="mk-port-panel-<%= i %>" aria-selected="<%= i.zero? %>"
                  <%= 'tabindex="-1"'.html_safe unless i.zero? %> data-index="<%= i %>"
                  data-funders-portfolio-target="tab"
                  data-action="click->funders-portfolio#choose mouseenter->funders-portfolio#choose focus->funders-portfolio#choose">
            <span class="mk-portfolio__item-icon mk-portfolio__item-icon--logo">
              <%# The org's own brand mark identifies it in the rail; the category glyph is a
                  fallback for any org without a logo asset. %>
              <% if org[:logo] %>
                <%= image_tag org[:logo], class: "mk-portfolio__item-logo", alt: "", loading: "eager", decoding: "async" %>
              <% else %>
                <%= inline_icon org[:icon], size: 22 %>
              <% end %>
            </span>
            <span class="mk-portfolio__item-text">
              <span class="mk-portfolio__item-name"><%= org[:name] %></span>
              <span class="mk-portfolio__item-sub"><%= org[:sub] %></span>
            </span>
            <span class="mk-portfolio__item-caret" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </button>
        <% end %>
        <button type="button" class="mk-portfolio__item mk-portfolio__item--open" role="tab"
                id="mk-port-tab-<%= wildcard_index %>" aria-controls="mk-port-panel-<%= wildcard_index %>"
                aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1" data-index="<%= wildcard_index %>" data-wildcard="true"
                data-funders-portfolio-target="tab"
                data-action="click->funders-portfolio#choose mouseenter->funders-portfolio#choose focus->funders-portfolio#choose">
          <span class="mk-portfolio__item-icon"><%= inline_icon "idea", size: 22 %></span>
          <span class="mk-portfolio__item-text">
            <span class="mk-portfolio__item-name">Something not here yet</span>
            <span class="mk-portfolio__item-sub">Fund a new organization, project, or idea</span>
          </span>
          <span class="mk-portfolio__item-caret" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
      </div>

        <%# Mobile-only cue: on narrow screens the rail stacks above a single visible panel, so
            signal that the rail is interactive (hidden ≥880px where rail + stage sit side by side). %>
        <p class="mk-portfolio__hint" aria-hidden="true">Tap any organization to see its story&nbsp;&darr;</p>
      </div>

      <%# --- stage: one detail panel per org, plus the open-door wildcard panel --- %>
      <div class="mk-portfolio__stage">
        <% recipients.each_with_index do |org, i| %>
          <%# No `hidden` in the markup: without JS every panel renders stacked (the controller
              hides non-active panels in connect, so nothing is hidden until enhanced). %>
          <div class="mk-portfolio__panel" role="tabpanel" id="mk-port-panel-<%= i %>"
               aria-labelledby="mk-port-tab-<%= i %>" data-funders-portfolio-target="panel">
            <figure class="mk-portfolio__media mk-portfolio__media--<%= org[:media] %>">
              <% if org[:media] == :terminal %>
                <%# Decorative CSS terminal-art cover (no logo/photo): faint "code" lines + a
                    blinking prompt. Purely presentational, so hidden from assistive tech. %>
                <div class="mk-portfolio__terminal" aria-hidden="true">
                  <span class="mk-portfolio__terminal-line"></span>
                  <span class="mk-portfolio__terminal-line"></span>
                  <span class="mk-portfolio__terminal-line"></span>
                  <span class="mk-portfolio__terminal-prompt">&#10095;<i class="mk-portfolio__terminal-cursor"></i></span>
                </div>
              <% else %>
                <%# Eager (not lazy): once enhanced, non-active panels are hidden, so a lazy image
                    wouldn't load until its panel is revealed — a blank banner on first swap. They're
                    a small, fixed set, so loading them up front is the right trade. The wordmark/logo
                    banner is decorative (the name is in the <h3>); only photos get descriptive alt. %>
                <%= image_tag org[:brand], class: "mk-portfolio__media-img",
                      alt: org[:media] == :photo ? org[:brand_alt] : "",
                      style: org[:focus] ? "object-position: #{org[:focus]}" : nil,
                      loading: "eager", decoding: "async" %>
              <% end %>
            </figure>

            <div class="mk-portfolio__body">
              <%# Main content is vertically centered in the card; the footer stays pinned to the
                  bottom, so lighter cards read as deliberately spaced rather than top-loaded. %>
              <div class="mk-portfolio__body-main">
                <h3 class="mk-portfolio__name"><%= org[:name] %></h3>
                <p class="mk-portfolio__what"><%= org[:what] %></p>

              <% if org[:stat] %>
                <div class="mk-portfolio__stat-row">
                  <span class="mk-portfolio__stat"><%= org[:stat] %></span>
                  <span class="mk-portfolio__stat-label"><%= org[:stat_label] %></span>
                </div>
              <% end %>

              <% if org[:facts] %>
                <ul class="mk-ticks mk-portfolio__facts">
                  <% org[:facts].each do |fact| %><li><%= sanitize fact, tags: %w[em] %></li><% end %>
                </ul>
              <% end %>

              <% if org[:quote] %>
                <figure class="mk-portfolio__quote">
                  <blockquote><%= org[:quote] %></blockquote>
                  <figcaption class="mk-portfolio__author">
                    <%= image_tag org[:author_avatar], class: "mk-portfolio__avatar",
                          alt: org[:author], width: 48, height: 48, loading: "lazy", decoding: "async" %>
                    <span class="mk-portfolio__author-meta">
                      <span class="mk-portfolio__author-name"><%= org[:author] %></span>
                      <span class="mk-portfolio__author-role"><%= org[:author_role] %></span>
                    </span>
                  </figcaption>
                </figure>
              <% end %>
              </div>

              <div class="mk-portfolio__footer">
                <% if org[:funded_by] %>
                  <%# This org's backer(s). Shown small, greyscaled, and clearly labeled so it reads
                      as "a real funder's money reached this org on HCB", never as an HCB customer.
                      "Backed by" (vs "Funded by") covers both grants and funding partnerships. %>
                  <div class="mk-portfolio__funded">
                    <span class="mk-portfolio__funded-label">Backed by</span>
                    <% org[:funded_by].each do |f| %>
                      <%= image_tag f[:logo], class: ["mk-portfolio__funder", f[:class]].compact.join(" "),
                            alt: f[:alt], loading: "lazy", decoding: "async" %>
                    <% end %>
                  </div>
                <% end %>
                <a class="mk-portfolio__visit" href="<%= org[:url] %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                  Visit <%= org[:name] %><span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;&rarr;</span>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        <% end %>

        <%# Open-door wildcard: the list is a sample, not a menu. Reframes the whole section so a
            funder never reads it as a closed directory, and lands the page's central wedge. %>
        <div class="mk-portfolio__panel mk-portfolio__panel--open" role="tabpanel"
             id="mk-port-panel-<%= wildcard_index %>" aria-labelledby="mk-port-tab-<%= wildcard_index %>"
             data-funders-portfolio-target="panel">
          <div class="mk-portfolio__body">
            <span class="mk-portfolio__open-mark"><%= inline_icon "idea", size: 30 %></span>
            <h3 class="mk-portfolio__name">Your pick doesn&rsquo;t have to be on this list, or on HCB yet.</h3>
            <p class="mk-portfolio__what">
              Fund any of the <%= @stats[:organizations] %> organizations already here, a brand-new
              project that isn&rsquo;t a 501(c)(3) yet, or an idea that&rsquo;s still just a team of one.
              You bring the pick; we get them running in days.
            </p>
            <div class="mk-portfolio__footer">
              <a class="marketing-btn marketing-btn--primary" href="#talk-to-us">Talk to our team</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ============================ FUNDERS MARQUEE ============================ %>
<%# Recognizable funders whose grants have reached organizations on HCB. The names are factual; these
    funders are not HCB customers, so the copy must not imply they "use" HCB. Text-only for now;
    swap to logos once assets + per-funder clearance are in hand. %>
<section class="mk-section">
  <div class="mk-container">
    <div class="mk-section__head">
      <p class="mk-eyebrow">In good company</p>
      <h2 class="mk-section__title">Major funders already back organizations on HCB.</h2>
    </div>
    <ul class="mk-funders" aria-label="Funders whose grants have reached organizations on HCB">
      <%# Ordered so the biggest names land where eyes go first (top row + left edge of each row).
          Excludes funders who only gave to Hack Club HQ itself, not to organizations on HCB. %>
      <li><%= image_tag "https://cdn.hackclub.com/019ed938-00a8-714d-bd51-3a7145ef976e/image.png", alt: "Ford Foundation", loading: "lazy", decoding: "async" %></li>
      <li><%= image_tag "https://cdn.hackclub.com/019ed938-0314-7502-9dca-4a7f342c53d7/image.png", alt: "Omidyar Network", loading: "lazy", decoding: "async" %></li>
